	<h2>Top Fence Styles That Add Value in Stockton</h2>

	<h3>1. Clean-Line Vinyl Privacy Fencing</h3>
	<p><strong>Best for:</strong> Backyard privacy, family homes, properties with pools</p>

	<p><strong>Why it adds value:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Delivers immediate privacy without waiting for material aging</li>
		<li>Zero maintenance requirement appeals to busy homebuyers</li>
		<li>25-30 year lifespan means buyers won't replace it</li>
		<li>Clean modern appearance photographs well in listings</li>
		<li>Won't fade, crack, or require painting in Stockton sun</li>
		<li>Withstands Central Valley temperature extremes without warping</li>
	</ul>

	<p><strong>Value-maximizing choices:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Color:</strong> White, tan, or gray (avoid bold colors that limit buyer appeal)</li>
		<li><strong>Style:</strong> Smooth tongue-and-groove or simple privacy design</li>
		<li><strong>Height:</strong> 6 feet for privacy (8 feet may be excessive for resale)</li>
		<li><strong>Quality tier:</strong> Mid-to-premium grade (economy vinyl looks cheap)</li>
		<li><strong>Gates:</strong> Matching vinyl gates with quality hardware</li>
	</ul>

	<p><strong>Typical value added:</strong> $6,500-10,000 on homes valued $350,000-550,000</p>

